# Agents Monitor — optional local overrides.
#
# Copy this file to ~/.config/agents-monitor/local.conf and uncomment any line
# you want to override. The plugin script reads this file at every refresh
# (every 30 seconds), so changes take effect on the next tick.
#
# IMPORTANT: this file is parsed AS DATA, not as bash. Only KEY=VALUE lines are
# recognized, and only keys in the allowlist below take effect. Any other line
# (including arbitrary shell commands) is silently ignored. This is deliberate
# — local.conf must NOT be a code-execution sink.
#
# Lines starting with # are comments. Surrounding whitespace and quotes around
# the value are stripped.
#
# --- Recognized keys ---

# FLAP_WINDOW=120
#   Flap detection window in seconds. A service is classified as 🟡 flapping
#   if its PID changes within this many seconds. Lower = more sensitive.
#   Must be a positive integer. Invalid values are ignored.

# --- Path overrides (env vars only) ---
#
# To override the install paths, set these in your shell environment BEFORE
# launching SwiftBar (NOT in local.conf — they're needed before this file is
# read):
#
#   export AGENTS_MONITOR_CONFIG_DIR="$HOME/.config/agents-monitor"
#   export AGENTS_MONITOR_CACHE_DIR="$HOME/.cache/agents-monitor"
#   export AGENTS_MONITOR_HELPER="$HOME/.local/bin/launchctl-user"
#
# In practice you should never need to change these.
